    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.04/2262: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-09T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 9, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>579. For the Ambassador and Counselor only. Department’s 573, September 9, 11
                    a.m. We have not yet taken up with the Japanese Ambassador the points outlined
                    in the Department’s telegram under reference except of course as we have
                    repeatedly covered the subject matter of the third and fourth paragraphs in the
                    course of conversations prior to the receipt by us of the Japanese Government’s
                    recent proposals. The Ambassador has made an appointment to see me on the
                    morning of September 10<note n="9" xml:id="d316fn9">See memorandum of September
                        10, 1941, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_613">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 613</ref>.</note> at which time I shall
                    expect, if opportune, to discuss the subject with him along the lines indicated
                    in the telegram above referred to.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
